sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: hixC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: hixC binding site for Salmonella typhimurium Hin recombinase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A 26 bp sequence of DNA composed of 12 bp inverted repeats and a 2 bp core that operates in Salmonella paired with a hixR binding site to recombine DNA. A second hix site is required for recombination to occur. The two sites bind Hin recombinase in the formation of an invertasome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Missouri Western and Davidson Groups, Todd Eckdahl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Nanassy and Hughes. 1998. In Vivo Identification of Intermediate Stages of the DNA Inversion Reaction Catlyzed by the Salmonella Hin Recombinase [http://www.genetics.org/cgi/content/abstract/149/4/1649]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Standard BioBrick prefix and suffix were added to the 26 bp sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J44002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the pBAD promoter (BBa_I13453) in the opposite orientation. It can be used to drive transcription in the direction of suffix to prefix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brad Ogden

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetA(C)f
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the coding region of the TetR gene. It requires a promoter and RBS for the cell to be able to express tetracyline resistance.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sabriya Rosemond, Erin Zwack
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was cloned into PsB1A2 plamsid.
